<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/15728:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Earle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-08T17:00:00+02:00">October 8,
                                    1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 9—7:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>410. My 394, September 24. The director of the press informs us that
                            every effort is being made to keep out of the Bulgarian press all
                            articles unfavorable to our country.</p>
                        <p>No such articles have now appeared for some time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>